org.metaborg.spoofax.shell.client.console

Class JLine2InputHistoryTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.metaborg.spoofax.shell.client.console.JLine2InputHistoryTest
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    JLine2PersistentInputHistoryTest

    public class JLine2InputHistoryTest
extends Object
    Tests the JLine2 history adapter. It tests the interplay between our interface and theirs: first history entries are added by user-simulation in setUp(String), and then the test operates on it via our interface, to see if it correctly implements an adapter towards the outside.

      • testAppend

        public final void testAppend()
        Tests whether the JLine2InputHistory.append(String) method correctly adds a new entry via our own interface. First tests on user-simulated input for two entries, and tests whether the entry at index 2 is out of bounds. Then a new entry is appended via our adapter, and the entry that was previously out of bound should now return the newly added entry.

      • testGetMostRecent

        public final void testGetMostRecent()
